Welcome to Fight Yard Taboo! This secret Prodigy training yard was buried amongst the endless tunnels and passage ways beep in the Prodigy military compound. Due to the small size and relatively close contact with the enemy a sharp eye and lightning fast reaction is needed to survive, everyone must constantly be on the move with very few places to camp this training yard will test your skills and your endurance! You will be dropped into Fight Yard Taboo with only your side arms, scattered around the yard are 7 HE nads. Hold on to these and make good use of them. If you chose to offer your participants alternative weapons let the noobs have there sniper rifles they’ll probably never get to use them! ;) -------------------------------------- Any way blah blah, foo bar… This map was created and intended to be run with CS:S DM (http://www.bailopan.net/cssdm/) How ever being a Beta release this offers me and the larger community to decide if weapons should be dropped into the map like normal "FY" maps or if buy zones should be added or leave it alone. I am open to any constructive criticism that improves this maps playability, I know CS:S DM is popular but not on every servers so if weapons are desirable please chime in! I can't get bzip2 to do it's thing right now vista has gone crazy so no .bz2 file right now, at 3.54Mb this map is small but a .bz2 does come in handy! I'll include this when I release a final map but most should know how to make it! -------------------------------------- Installing is simple copy or move fy_taboo_beta.bsp and fy_taboo_beta.nav to your map folder, normally found at: C:\Program Files\Steam\SteamApps\STEAM_ID\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps -------------------------------------- Project page: http://www.fpsbanana.com/studios/projects/view/20680 Enjoy! Welcome to Fight Yard Taboo! This secret Prodigy training yard was buried amongst the endless tunnels and passage ways beep in the Prodigy military compound. Due to the small size and relatively close contact with the enemy a sharp eye and lightning fast reaction is needed to survive, everyone must constantly be on the move with very few places to camp this training yard will test your skills and your endurance! You will be dropped into Fight Yard Taboo with only your side arms, scattered around the yard are 7 HE nads. Hold on to these and make good use of them. If you chose to offer your participants alternative weapons let the noobs have there sniper rifles they’ll probably never get to use them! ;)
This map was created and intended to be run with CS:S DM (http://www.bailopan.net/cssdm/) CS:S DM is not required and the buy zones will work with out it!!

Installing

Unzip taboo.zip and copy or move fy_taboo.bsp and fy_taboo.nav to your map folder, normally found at: C:\Program Files\Steam\SteamApps\STEAM_ID\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps

Server Files

There are two extra folder in the zip file, if your only wanting to play this map with bots you wont need them, however since most maps here find a home on servers I'm including bz2 versions fy_taboo.bsp.bz2 fy_taboo.nav.bz2 copy these files to your servers maps folder! Lastly, if you have cssdm installed and want utter chaos, check out cfg\cssdm\spawns and have upto 32 players spawn in 58 random locations around the map!
Project page: http://www.fpsbanana.com/studios/projects/view/20680 Enjoy! Jason, AKA GrayTap, The Black Llama

FY SUMMERPOOL BY UNREAL I got a sudden inspiration to make a map related to summer, so I remembered the old fy_poolday map that I used to play so much before I was even mapper. So I came up with this, a totally new version of fy_poolday, it has much more detail, and a nice ambient. Features: > nice environment > fishes > custom textures/models > drops > buyzone > bombsite (inside the pool) > 2 secondary roots I tried to keep everything like the original one, just changing the style, so thats the final result. Special thanks to TopHATTwaffle for providing really unique custom textures, and to whoever created the original version, I'm sorry, there are so many versions I simply don't know who is the real author. I hope you like it, Have fun.
